Gá»i cuá»‘n (Vietnamese spring rolls) were made by rolling up dampened bÃ¡nh trÃ¡ng (rice paper) to wrap the 
ingredients of choice (I used a customary combination of pork belly, king prawns, rice vermicelli, carrot 
& cucumber strands, bean sprouts, lettuce, mint, coriander, and Chinese chive). To make the nÆ°á»›c cháº¥m sauce, 
